I think we should take the chance.

10
00:01:21,410 --> 00:01:22,490
Worth a shot when desperate.

11
00:01:23,410 --> 00:01:24,990
Did you check when the eclipse is?

12
00:01:26,580 --> 00:01:27,420
This Saturday.

13
00:01:27,990 --> 00:01:29,290
- Tomorrow.
- Tomorrow?

14
00:01:29,290 --> 00:01:30,130
So soon?

15
00:01:30,950 --> 00:01:31,950
But I'm worried,

16
00:01:32,580 --> 00:01:34,540
what if we don't switch back?

17
00:01:35,950 --> 00:01:37,290
Then we'll just keep trying.

18
00:01:37,490 --> 00:01:38,950
The President's still in the country.

19
00:01:38,990 --> 00:01:39,990
We can find him again.

20
00:01:40,870 --> 00:01:42,740
If we fail this time,

21
00:01:43,160 --> 00:01:44,000
you should come stay

22
00:01:44,010 --> 00:01:45,040
at my place for a bit.

23
00:01:45,290 --> 00:01:46,490
Your mom keeps mentioning you,

24
00:01:46,540 --> 00:01:47,980
"Chen Jing'an is so thoughtful.

25
00:01:47,980 --> 00:01:49,040
Hope she visits us often."

26
00:01:49,040 --> 00:01:49,880
Okay.

27
00:01:55,160 --> 00:01:56,240
Before I realized,

28
00:01:56,240 --> 00:01:58,160
Li Minqiu had been gone for days.

29
00:02:01,410 --> 00:02:02,250
Chen Jing'an,

30
00:02:03,330 --> 00:02:04,830
my gut tells me

31
00:02:05,740 --> 00:02:06,830
Li Minqiu's leaving

32
00:02:07,490 --> 00:02:08,450
is just the beginning.

33
00:02:09,200 --> 00:02:11,330
More things will happen next.

34
00:02:12,080 --> 00:02:13,080
We'll see.

35
00:02:14,540 --> 00:02:15,700
Stop talking nonsense.

36
00:02:22,370 --> 00:02:23,620
Let's go on a picnic tomorrow.

37
00:02:24,160 --> 00:02:25,000
Picnic?

38
00:02:26,080 --> 00:02:28,080
Tomorrow might have the solar eclipse.

39
00:02:28,580 --> 00:02:29,620
The President said

40
00:02:29,740 --> 00:02:30,700
this eclipse

41
00:02:30,700 --> 00:02:31,700
has a high chance

42
00:02:31,700 --> 00:02:33,200
of altering magnetic fields,

43
00:02:33,450 --> 00:02:34,290
meaning

44
00:02:34,330 --> 00:02:35,870
Zhu Niannian and I could switch back.

45
00:02:37,580 --> 00:02:38,910
Since we're so close,

46
00:02:39,120 --> 00:02:40,620
shouldn't we spend this big day

47
00:02:40,620 --> 00:02:41,080
together?

48
00:02:41,490 --> 00:02:43,200
Perfect!

49
00:02:43,290 --> 00:02:44,830
I'll bring tons of snacks.

50
00:02:45,080 --> 00:02:45,990
Once you switch back,

51
00:02:45,990 --> 00:02:47,330
you can visit my place.

52
00:02:47,540 --> 00:02:49,450
My mom won't stop talking about you.

53
00:02:55,120 --> 00:02:57,040
I'll go find Niannian, Shasha, and Changning.

54
00:02:58,450 --> 00:03:00,160
(Not just the two of us?)

55
00:03:03,160 --> 00:03:04,540
I was about to find you.

56
00:03:04,790 --> 00:03:06,080
Let's have a group meal tomorrow

57
00:03:06,370 --> 00:03:08,160
and witness my switch in person.

58
00:03:08,450 --> 00:03:09,290
Sure.

59
00:03:09,580 --> 00:03:10,800
I'll ask for a day off.

60
00:03:11,620 --> 00:03:12,660
I'll go find the girls.

61
00:03:12,950 --> 00:03:13,790
Wait.

62
00:03:18,620 --> 00:03:19,910
Are you free tonight?

63
